vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}

title: "ComponentColumn Type Erasure" {
  near: top-center
  shape: text
  style: {
    font-size: 28
    bold: true
    underline: true
  }
}

direction: right

ColumnOps_Trait: "trait ColumnOps" {
  style: {
    fill: "#E8D5E0"
    stroke: "#7B5E7B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  shape: class
  "+ as_any(&self)": "&dyn Any"
  "+ as_any_mut(&mut self)": "&mut dyn Any"
  "+ len(&self)": "usize"
  "+ swap_remove(&mut self, index: usize)": "Option<usize>"
  "+ push_raw(&mut self, component: Box<dyn Any>)": "void"
  "+ get_raw(&self, index: usize)": "Option<&dyn Any>"
  "+ get_raw_mut(&mut self, index: usize)": "Option<&mut dyn Any>"
  "+ clear(&mut self)": "void"
  "+ reserve(&mut self, additional: usize)": "void"
}

Vec_T: "struct Vec<T>" {
  style: {
    fill: "#B5D8EB"
    stroke: "#4A90A4"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  shape: class
  "- data: RawVec<T>"
  "+ as_any(&self)": "&dyn Any { self }"
  "+ as_any_mut(&mut self)": "&mut dyn Any { self }"
  "+ len(&self)": "usize { Vec::len(self) }"
  "+ swap_remove(&mut self, idx: usize)": "Option<usize>"
  "+ push_raw(&mut self, comp: Box<dyn Any>)": "{ self.push(*comp.downcast::<T>()) }"
}

ComponentColumn: "struct ComponentColumn" {
  style: {
    fill: "#C7F1C6"
    stroke: "#5A8F5A"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  shape: class
  "+ type_id: TypeId"
  "- storage: Box<dyn ColumnOps>"
  "+ component_size: usize"
  "+ type_name: &'static str"
  "+ new<T: 'static>()": "Self"
  "+ push<T>(&mut self, component: T)": "void"
  "+ get<T>(&self, index: usize)": "Option<&T>"
  "+ get_mut<T>(&mut self, index: usize)": "Option<&mut T>"
  "+ as_vec<T>(&self)": "Option<&Vec<T>>"
  "+ as_vec_mut<T>(&mut self)": "Option<&mut Vec<T>>"
  "+ swap_remove(&mut self, index: usize)": "Option<usize>"
}

Vec_T -> ColumnOps_Trait: "implements trait" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4A90A4"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 5
  }
  target-arrowhead: {
    shape: triangle
    style.filled: false
  }
}

ComponentColumn -> ColumnOps_Trait: "storage: Box<dyn ColumnOps>" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#5A8F5A"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
  source-arrowhead: {
    shape: diamond
    style.filled: true
  }
}

Legend: {
  near: bottom-right
  style: {
    fill: "#F5F5F5"
    stroke: "#CCCCCC"
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
  Trait_Legend: "◀─── implements (trait)" {
    shape: text
    style.font-size: 12
  }
  Compose_Legend: "──◆ owns (composition)" {
    shape: text
    style.font-size: 12
  }
  Type_Erasure_Legend: "Box<dyn Trait>" {
    shape: text
    style: {
      font-size: 12
      italic: true
    }
  }
}

Pattern_Explanation: |'md
**Type Erasure Pattern (Type-Safe Wrappers)**
1. `ColumnOps` trait defines common operations (len, swap, push_raw).
2. `Vec<T>` implements trait for any `T: 'static`.
3. `ComponentColumn` stores `Box<dyn ColumnOps>` (Type Erasure).
4. Type info is preserved via a `TypeId` field to ensure safe downcasting.
5. The `as_vec<T>` method uses `storage.as_any().downcast_ref::<Vec<T>>()`.

**Trade-offs:**
- **Pro:** Enables storage of heterogeneous columns in a single `HashMap`.
- **Pro:** Preserves strict type safety through runtime `TypeId` checks.
- **Con:** Heap allocation per column container.
- **Con:** Virtual dispatch overhead for generic ops.
'| {
  near: bottom-left
  style: {
    fill: "#FFF9E6"
    stroke: "#E6C200"
    stroke-width: 1
  }
}

Memory_Layout: |'md
**Memory Layout Analysis (x86_64)**

`ComponentColumn` (Stack-allocated Wrapper)
| Offset | Field | Size | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 0x00 | `type_id` | 8B | Unique ID for type `T` |
| 0x08 | `storage.ptr` | 8B | Pointer to concrete `Vec<T>` data |
| 0x10 | `storage.vtable` | 8B | Pointer to `ColumnOps` vtable |
| 0x18 | `comp_size` | 8B | `mem::size_of::<T>()` |
| 0x20 | `type_name.ptr` | 8B | Metadata string pointer |
| 0x28 | `type_name.len` | 8B | Metadata string length |

**Heap Allocation (`Vec<T>`)**
- **Header (24B):** `[DataPtr: 8B | Cap: 8B | Len: 8B]`
- **Buffer:** Contiguous array `[T; Capacity]`

*sizeof = 48 bytes (0x30)*
'| {
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#E6F3FF"
    stroke: "#4A90A4"
    stroke-width: 1
    font: mono
  }
}